18/05/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Vladica Simonovic, head of the "Family of Serb Supporters" group was questioned on Thursday (May 15th) at Belgrade's 4th Municipal Court, for allegedly threatening President Boris Tadic and Deputy Prime Minister Bozidar Djelic.
The group is suspected of placing posters of the two -- titled "Enemy of the State" -- around Belgrade after they recently signed the Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU.
(Beta, B92, Tanjug, RTS - 16/05/08)
